author: Erika Kim
title: Gap Unveils ‘90s Archive Re-Issue Collection With “Generation Gap” Film
text:
Visit the original post to see all 7 images from this gallery. 
There is no denial that the past five years have been a renaissance of the the 1990s, especially when it comes to fashion.
Paying tribute to the legendary Gap ads of the ’90s, the campaign features Lizzy Jagger, TJ Mizell, Evan Ross, Chelsea Tyler, Rumor Willis, Coco Gordon, and Naomi Campbell, who wore the Pocket Tee re-issue as a nod to her 1992 Pocket Tee ad.
Gap revealed the 90’s archive collection with a new film titled “Generation Gap” with appearances from all the children of the stars that originally starred in the iconic Gap ads from the ’90s.
Featuring iconic styles from the ’90s—from the bodysuit to the pocket tee—the ’90s archive re-issue collection will be available for purchase starting February 7.
